title: Brentford vs Arsenal - English Premier League 2024/25 Week 19

title: Aston Villa vs Brighton and Hove Albion - English Premier League 2024/25 Week 19
description: Aston Villa lost their last Premier League meeting with Brighton 1-0 in May, having won five in a row against the Seagulls before this. Brighton have won just one of their 14 away league games against Aston Villa, losing the last three in a row including a 6-1 loss last season.

title: Real Valladolid vs Valencia - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 17
description: Real Valladolid have won just one of their last 10 home games against Valencia in LaLiga, although that was the most recent in January 2023. The Valladolid side have not won back-to-back home games against Valencia in the competition since a run of three wins between 1983 and 1985. Valencia have won five of their last six matches against Real Valladolid in LaLiga, having drawn five of their previous six meetings in the competition prior.

title: Mallorca vs Girona - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 17
description: This will be the fifth meeting between Mallorca and Girona in LaLiga. The Balearic side have not lost either of their two home games against the Catalan side in the competition, while losing both of their visits to the Municipal de Montilivi. In all competitions, Mallorca have won their last two meetings with Girona, and could win 3+ games in a row against the Catalan side for the first time.

title: Sevilla vs Celta de Vigo - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 17
description: Sevilla have not won any of their last five matches against Celta Vigo in LaLiga, and, should they fail to win here, they will suffer their longest winless run against the Galician side in their top-flight history. Celta Vigo are unbeaten in each of their last three visits to the Ramon Sánchez-Pizjuán in LaLiga, after having lost eight of their previous 11 away games against Sevilla in the competition.

title: UEFA Nations League .. Portugal The Champion
description: The 2024/25 season marked the fourth edition of the UEFA Nations League, with fierce competition between the top-tier teams, led by stars such as Mbappe, Dembele, Lamine Yamal, and Ronaldo. Defending champions Spain, who won the 2023 tournament, lost the final to Portugal 5-3 on penalties after a 2-2 draw after regulation and extra time. Portuguese star Ronaldo lifted the trophy once again.

title: Villarreal vs Real Betis - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 17
description: Villarreal have not won any of their last three home games against Real Betis in LaLiga, while only once before have they failed to win in more games in a row against them in top-flight, doing so in their first six games against Real Betis in the competition. Villarreal have not won either of their last two LaLiga home games against Real Betis, although only once before have they gone three games without a win at La Cerámica against them, doing so in their first three home meetings with the Andalusian side in the competition.

title: Espanyol vs Osasuna - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 17
description: Espanyol have not won any of their last six games against Osasuna in LaLiga, and could equal their longest winless run against the Navarrese side in the competition, suffered between 1987 and 1991. Osasuna are unbeaten in their last three visits to Espanyol in LaLiga, drawing the last two. Osasuna have never drawn 3+ successive away games against Espanyol in the top-flight.

description: Advanced to 18 December 2024 while the other eight fixtures will be played in January 2025, the 16th round of Ligue 1 is the second matchday in the competitions history to be played in two different years without being interrupted by fixtures on another round after MD22 in 1995-96. Monaco will become the opponent most often faced by Paris in Ligue 1. ASM are also the team that has won the most games against PSG in the top-flight.

title: Nice vs Rennes - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 16
description: This is the third year in a row that Nice and Rennes face each other in their first Ligue 1 match of the year, though the previous two took place in Rennes with Rennes winning both. This is the fifth time in a row that Le Gym has started a calendar year against a Breton club after a 2-0 defeat in 2021 and 3-0 win in 2022, both against Brest. Nice have won 43 matches against Rennes in Ligue 1, their-joint most versus any opponent. Le Gym have lost only three of their last 18 games against SRFC in the top-flight.

title: Angers SCO vs Brest - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 16
description: Angers and Brest will face each other for the 11th time in Ligue 1. After winning only one of their first eight duels in the top-flight, Brest have won the last two. Angers have not found the net in their last two Ligue 1 matches and could go three games without scoring in the same season in the top-flight for the first time since March 2023.

title: Saint-Étienne vs Reims - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 16
description: St Etienne have lost four of their last six Ligue 1 matches against Reims after going unbeaten in the previous 16. St Etienne have lost only one of their last 21 visits to Reims in Ligue 1, but it was the most recent one in May 2022. You have to go back to 1952-1954 to see Les Verts lose multiple games in a row against the Champagne side in the top-flight.

title: Lille vs Nantes - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 16
description: Lille have not lost to Nantes in Ligue 1 since September 2015, a 1-0 success for the Canaries in the North. Les Dogues are on a 17-game unbeaten run against FCN, the longest run in their history in the top-flight against the same opponent. Lille have not lost any of their last 17 matches in all competitions, the second longest unbeaten streak in their history after a 19-game run between October 1973 and March 1974.

title: Olympique Lyonnais vs Montpellier - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 16
description: Lyon and Montpellier will face each other for the 60th time in Ligue 1. Among the current clubs in the top-flight, MHSC are the third team against which Les Gones have won most often, behind Strasbourg and Angers. Montpellier have lost five of their last six meetings with Lyon, having won each of the previous three. MHSCs last two wins over OL have come on the road.

title: Olympique Marseille vs Le Havre - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 16
description: Marseille are on a 20-game unbeaten run against Le Havre in Ligue 1, having only had a longer streak without defeat against a single opponent once before. OM even has a 100%-win rate in six matches against Le Havre in Ligue 1 in the 21st century, the opponent they have faced the most over that period while posting such a perfect record. Marseille have lost only one of their 20 home matches against Le Havre in Ligue 1 and it came in the first of those back in December 1938. OM have only faced Bastia more often at home while losing at most once in the top-flight.

title: Lens vs Toulouse - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 16
description: Lens have won each of their last six Ligue 1 matches against Toulouse and could establish their longest winning streak in the top-flight against a single opponent.
